cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.HC, cs.GR 

The paper deals with a dataset of interaction and influence spreading in a virtual world platform. The study involves analyzing the spreading campaigns and building a multilayer network to place the campaigns in a wider context. The paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC), Cybersecurity and Privacy (cs.CYBER), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), and Graphics (cs.GR).
